Name: Boston
Description: Boston is the capital and largest city of Massachusetts and the largest city in New England in the northeast of the United States. Boston is located on the Atlantic coast in the northeast of the United States. Founded in 1630, it is one of the oldest and most culturally valuable cities in the United States. The Boston Tea dumping incident in American history finally led to the famous American War of independence.

Name: Los Angeles
Description: Los Angeles, located in the southwest of California, is the second largest city in the United States and the largest city in the western United States. It is often called "City of Angels".

Name: Cheyenne, Wyoming
Description: Cheyenne is the capital and largest city of Wyoming, the largest city in the state and the county seat of Laramie county.

Name: Suzhou
Description: Suzhou is one of the first batch of national famous historical and cultural cities with a history of nearly 2500 years. It is an important birthplace of Wu culture and has the reputation of "paradise on earth". Suzhou classical gardens and China Grand Canal (Suzhou section), representatives of Chinese private gardens, are listed as world cultural heritage by UNESCO.

Name: Augusta, Maine
Description: Augusta is a city located in kennabek County, Maine. It was built in 1621 and became the state capital in 1831. It is also the capital of Maine and the county seat of kennabek county. Nearby are typical New England landscapes, forested hills and beautiful glacial lakes. Summer resort.
